1
00:00:00,340 --> 00:00:01,640
(All people, incidents,
and backgrounds...)

2
00:00:01,640 --> 00:00:03,380
(in this drama are fictitious
and unrelated to reality.)

3
00:00:03,380 --> 00:00:05,240
(Also, children were filmed
under production guidelines.)

4
00:00:06,640 --> 00:00:08,050
(Episode 51)

5
00:00:09,210 --> 00:00:11,520
Soon, I'll be able to use Choi Yu Na
to take down Chairman Park Tae Ho...

6
00:00:12,650 --> 00:00:14,920
and end this once and for all.

7
00:00:18,120 --> 00:00:19,120
Chloe.

8
00:00:21,660 --> 00:00:22,660
You need to see this.

9
00:00:23,530 --> 00:00:25,400
Everyone's freaking out,
saying Oh Jung Ran is a murderer.

10
00:00:28,070 --> 00:00:30,440
Apparently, this all blew up
while we were at the hospital.

11
00:00:30,870 --> 00:00:32,070
The accusations are shocking.

12
00:00:32,900 --> 00:00:34,770
It says she killed
Chairman Park Tae Ho's first wife...

13
00:00:35,170 --> 00:00:36,370
and took her place.

14
00:00:37,480 --> 00:00:38,780
(Is Oh Jung Ran, the wife
of Adele Group's chairman, a murderer?)

15
00:00:38,840 --> 00:00:41,380
If it's true,
it's definitely shocking.

16
00:00:42,480 --> 00:00:44,980
I'm going to find out for sure
if it's true.

17
00:00:45,420 --> 00:00:46,480
If it is,

18
00:00:47,750 --> 00:00:49,720
you are absolutely
not marrying Park Hyun Jun.

19
00:00:54,360 --> 00:00:57,230
Got it? Why aren't you answering me?

20
00:01:09,540 --> 00:01:10,540
Hyun Jun.

21
00:01:12,080 --> 00:01:13,310
Are you not angry anymore?

22
00:01:13,950 --> 00:01:15,380
Is that why you came to see me?

23
00:01:17,180 --> 00:01:18,880
Mom, about those rumors...

24
00:01:19,480 --> 00:01:23,520
Don't you worry about that.
I'll handle it soon.

25
00:01:23,960 --> 00:01:27,030
We're releasing a rebuttal,
and your father promised to help.

26
00:01:27,260 --> 00:01:28,490
So don't give it a second thought.

27
00:01:28,960 --> 00:01:31,460
Just hold your head high
like you always do.

28
00:01:31,930 --> 00:01:32,930
All right?

29
00:01:34,670 --> 00:01:35,670
Hold my head high?

30
00:01:38,970 --> 00:01:40,670
Then I guess
we should clear this up.

31
00:01:41,240 --> 00:01:42,240
What?

32
00:01:42,510 --> 00:01:45,540
Hyun Jun, what's gotten into you?
Where are we going?

33
00:01:45,640 --> 00:01:48,310
(Police Station)

34
00:01:48,610 --> 00:01:51,350
What are we doing
at the police station this late?

35
00:01:52,880 --> 00:01:54,050
Turn yourself in.

36
00:01:56,290 --> 00:01:57,290
What?

37
00:01:58,890 --> 00:02:00,290
Why would I turn myself in?

38
00:02:01,690 --> 00:02:03,930
You took a life.
You have to be punished.

39
00:02:05,260 --> 00:02:06,460
What do you mean I took a life?

40
00:02:07,230 --> 00:02:09,730
How can you of all people doubt me?

41
00:02:10,270 --> 00:02:12,440
I keep telling you,
Kim Myung Hui made it all up.

42
00:02:13,300 --> 00:02:14,770
I already looked into it myself.

43
00:02:17,140 --> 00:02:18,140
You did?

44
00:02:19,140 --> 00:02:22,050
What did you find out?

45
00:02:23,750 --> 00:02:25,050
Tell it to the police.

46
00:02:26,650 --> 00:02:27,650
Hey!

47
00:02:28,220 --> 00:02:29,450
It's all in the past.

48
00:02:31,990 --> 00:02:33,690
The statute of limitations is up.

49
00:02:33,690 --> 00:02:35,390
What can the police do
without proof?

50
00:02:39,600 --> 00:02:40,600
No.

51
00:02:43,300 --> 00:02:45,270
No, that's not how it works.

52
00:02:48,040 --> 00:02:49,370
"I have nothing to hide."

53
00:02:49,970 --> 00:02:51,840
"I'm innocent,
so take me to the police."

54
00:02:51,840 --> 00:02:53,110
That's what you should be saying.

55
00:02:55,810 --> 00:02:58,150
If they're just rumors like you say,
that's how you should act.

56
00:03:00,790 --> 00:03:02,620
What are you saying?

57
00:03:04,660 --> 00:03:06,460
You mean you did this on purpose?

58
00:03:07,530 --> 00:03:08,530
That's right.

59
00:03:11,030 --> 00:03:14,030
I tried to convince myself
that the truth didn't matter.

60
00:03:16,670 --> 00:03:19,300
But I couldn't bring myself
to face Chloe.

61
00:03:20,510 --> 00:03:21,510
The thought of her...

62
00:03:23,980 --> 00:03:26,140
seeing me as a murderer's son
terrified me.

63
00:03:29,880 --> 00:03:32,550
Do you know what I wished for
on the way here?

64
00:03:35,790 --> 00:03:38,190
I hoped they were just rumors,
like you said.

65
00:03:39,920 --> 00:03:42,590
I wanted to be able
to proudly tell Chloe...

66
00:03:42,590 --> 00:03:44,030
that my mother didn't kill anyone.

67
00:03:44,100 --> 00:03:45,700
Do you know how badly I wanted that?

68
00:03:47,230 --> 00:03:48,230
Hyun...

69
00:03:50,340 --> 00:03:51,340
Hyun Jun.

70
00:03:54,940 --> 00:03:55,970
Get your hands off me.

71
00:03:57,710 --> 00:04:00,750
Get your murderous hands off me.

72
00:04:04,820 --> 00:04:06,120
You don't...

73
00:04:10,460 --> 00:04:11,590
have a son anymore.

74
00:04:14,260 --> 00:04:17,260
The moment I found out
you were a murderer,

75
00:04:20,870 --> 00:04:22,130
I died too.

76
00:04:24,970 --> 00:04:25,970
What?

77
00:04:26,370 --> 00:04:29,340
The Park Hyun Jun
who always held his head so high?

78
00:04:30,170 --> 00:04:31,380
The son...

79
00:04:36,180 --> 00:04:39,220
The son who tried so desperately
to understand his mother?

80
00:04:43,860 --> 00:04:45,120
He just died.

81
00:04:52,200 --> 00:04:53,360
Hyun Jun.

82
00:04:54,470 --> 00:04:55,770
Park Hyun Jun!

83
00:05:09,950 --> 00:05:12,320
Why shouldn't I be allowed...

84
00:05:12,850 --> 00:05:15,950
to kill the people
who murdered my father?

85
00:05:17,620 --> 00:05:18,890
You really are...

86
00:05:19,260 --> 00:05:21,090
your father's son, after all.

87
00:05:21,890 --> 00:05:24,660
I don't care what you say.

88
00:05:25,530 --> 00:05:27,400
I'll see this through to the end.

89
00:05:29,830 --> 00:05:30,970
How...

90
00:05:32,300 --> 00:05:34,740
How can I possibly protect you?

91
00:05:44,020 --> 00:05:45,080
Are you okay?

92
00:05:45,320 --> 00:05:46,320
What now?

93
00:05:47,690 --> 00:05:49,390
What do you want?

94
00:05:51,290 --> 00:05:54,330
I was just worried
about your mother.

95
00:06:07,140 --> 00:06:08,340
You're not worried.

96
00:06:10,810 --> 00:06:12,110
You're feeling guilty.

97
00:06:14,380 --> 00:06:16,510
The rumor
that my mom's a murderer...

98
00:06:17,150 --> 00:06:18,720
has your mother's fingerprints
all over it.

99
00:06:21,190 --> 00:06:22,390
Don't you think
pretending to be worried...

100
00:06:22,950 --> 00:06:24,390
just to ease your own conscience...

101
00:06:27,160 --> 00:06:28,630
is incredibly selfish?

102
00:06:49,150 --> 00:06:50,650
I get where Hyun Jun is coming from.

103
00:06:51,550 --> 00:06:54,420
So even if it hurts your feelings,
please try to understand.

104
00:06:56,950 --> 00:06:58,520
Of course, I understand.

105
00:06:59,020 --> 00:07:00,890
You don't have to worry
about my feelings.

106
00:07:03,730 --> 00:07:04,930
But from now on,

107
00:07:05,330 --> 00:07:07,900
please make sure we compete fairly.

108
00:07:27,750 --> 00:07:31,160
While I've lost my son...

109
00:07:34,430 --> 00:07:36,530
While my Hyun Jun
has been taken from me...

110
00:07:47,540 --> 00:07:48,540
Mrs. Ok.

111
00:07:48,870 --> 00:07:49,910
Yes, sir.

112
00:07:52,210 --> 00:07:54,310
Wait, where are the other two?

113
00:07:54,750 --> 00:07:56,350
Hyun Jun left early.

114
00:07:58,320 --> 00:08:01,090
Ms. Oh has lost her appetite.

115
00:08:01,990 --> 00:08:03,790
Oh Jung Ran lost her appetite?

116
00:08:04,220 --> 00:08:08,530
The gossip about her past
seems to be affecting her.

117
00:08:09,330 --> 00:08:10,330
Unbelievable.

118
00:08:10,660 --> 00:08:13,530
If she'd just lay low,
I would've taken care of it.

119
00:08:14,170 --> 00:08:16,470
She always has to be so dramatic.

120
00:08:22,240 --> 00:08:24,740
Scrub all the online posts
about my wife,

121
00:08:25,280 --> 00:08:27,880
and release a counter-statement
to put this to bed.

122
00:08:28,310 --> 00:08:30,180
- Yes, sir.
- Good.

123
00:08:35,450 --> 00:08:36,450
What is it?

124
00:08:37,660 --> 00:08:41,330
Is there a problem with me trying
to stop these rumors about my wife?

125
00:08:42,460 --> 00:08:44,160
It's not that
I have a problem with it.

126
00:08:45,000 --> 00:08:46,200
It's just a little strange.

127
00:08:47,000 --> 00:08:50,200
Why aren't you suspicious
of your wife at all?

128
00:08:51,470 --> 00:08:55,270
Your late wife
might have been murdered,

129
00:08:55,970 --> 00:08:57,910
but you seem to be brushing it off
so easily.

130
00:09:04,520 --> 00:09:08,790
Munhwadang's chairman's daughter
was seriously ill,

131
00:09:08,850 --> 00:09:10,090
and back then,

132
00:09:10,320 --> 00:09:12,360
Oh Jung Ran wasn't someone
who'd do such a thing.

133
00:09:12,590 --> 00:09:16,190
I know better than anyone
what was happening at the time,

134
00:09:16,590 --> 00:09:18,460
so I have no reason to doubt her.

135
00:09:19,660 --> 00:09:20,670
Myung Hui.

136
00:09:24,870 --> 00:09:28,240
Don't go around suspecting people
without a shred of evidence.

137
00:09:29,140 --> 00:09:31,040
And don't start a fight
with my wife...

138
00:09:31,640 --> 00:09:35,810
over something
that could damage Adele's name.

139
00:09:38,720 --> 00:09:42,120
I warned you to only go as far
as I'd be willing to overlook.

140
00:09:43,790 --> 00:09:45,360
Don't you forget it.

141
00:09:53,800 --> 00:09:56,400
She wasn't capable of murder?

142
00:09:59,740 --> 00:10:00,910
I see...

143
00:10:02,540 --> 00:10:04,010
you're still very interested in me.

144
00:10:05,580 --> 00:10:08,410
Honestly, I can't help but wonder.

145
00:10:08,750 --> 00:10:12,880
With rumors this wild,
you'd think he'd be suspicious.

146
00:10:13,580 --> 00:10:15,650
But the chairman doesn't seem
to care about the death...

147
00:10:15,750 --> 00:10:17,720
of Munhwadang's chairman's daughter.

148
00:10:18,320 --> 00:10:21,790
Could it be that he knew all along?

149
00:10:22,590 --> 00:10:23,590
Right.

150
00:10:24,800 --> 00:10:27,100
Thanks to you, I'm certain now.

151
00:10:28,100 --> 00:10:30,530
Back then and even now,

152
00:10:30,770 --> 00:10:32,040
Park Tae Ho chose me...

153
00:10:32,340 --> 00:10:33,900
over his wife from Munhwadang.

154
00:10:35,510 --> 00:10:37,480
- Are you saying...
- Park Tae Ho...

155
00:10:38,010 --> 00:10:39,680
will never leave me.

156
00:10:40,640 --> 00:10:41,650
Because...

157
00:10:42,210 --> 00:10:44,080
there are things only I can do.

158
00:10:45,820 --> 00:10:47,080
Just you wait.

159
00:10:48,020 --> 00:10:51,590
I'm going to show you exactly
what it is that only I can do.

160
00:10:53,360 --> 00:10:55,890
For everything you took from me,

161
00:10:56,890 --> 00:11:00,360
I've decided
to take the same from you.

162
00:11:13,940 --> 00:11:16,850
Listen.
The rumors will be dealt with.

163
00:11:19,050 --> 00:11:21,220
Then what about Kim Myung Hui?

164
00:11:23,650 --> 00:11:26,190
I've given her a clear warning.

165
00:11:28,930 --> 00:11:33,400
Of course.
You always go easy on her.

166
00:11:34,430 --> 00:11:36,400
I solved your problem, didn't I?

167
00:11:38,070 --> 00:11:39,370
Be that as it may,

168
00:11:40,600 --> 00:11:42,140
what are you going to do
about Chloe?

169
00:11:43,510 --> 00:11:46,840
To take over our bio division,

170
00:11:47,180 --> 00:11:51,220
she said she'd find
the perfect time and place...

171
00:11:51,880 --> 00:11:53,550
to kill me.

172
00:11:54,990 --> 00:11:57,560
So? How are you going to handle her?

173
00:11:58,890 --> 00:12:01,530
She's looking
for the perfect time and place,

174
00:12:02,890 --> 00:12:04,560
but I'll be the one to decide that.

175
00:12:05,230 --> 00:12:06,230
You?

176
00:12:07,770 --> 00:12:09,600
When and where?

177
00:12:11,000 --> 00:12:15,310
Talk to Manager Kang
and make a plausible fake schedule.

178
00:12:15,840 --> 00:12:20,380
Since the warehouse is isolated,
handling the cameras will be easy.

179
00:12:20,880 --> 00:12:22,880
Have Choi Yu Na lure...

180
00:12:23,680 --> 00:12:25,450
Chloe there.

181
00:12:25,950 --> 00:12:29,650
I'm going to show Chloe
just how terrifying...

182
00:12:31,520 --> 00:12:33,390
Park Tae Ho can really be.

183
00:12:34,930 --> 00:12:35,930
I see.

184
00:12:37,060 --> 00:12:38,600
The warehouse, you say?

185
00:12:48,610 --> 00:12:52,640
The herbal medicine you got
sure works wonders, doesn't it?

186
00:12:52,740 --> 00:12:57,520
How long has it been since you felt
well enough to eat like this?

187
00:12:58,020 --> 00:12:59,080
You're right.

188
00:13:00,150 --> 00:13:02,120
Strange.
I'm even getting my appetite back.

189
00:13:03,250 --> 00:13:04,920
Should I go get another batch today?

190
00:13:05,190 --> 00:13:08,960
And you call yourself a father?
Can't you see your own daughter?

191
00:13:09,060 --> 00:13:10,130
Just look at her.

192
00:13:10,390 --> 00:13:12,860
We should be worried
about her now, not you.

193
00:13:13,060 --> 00:13:15,330
Why? What's wrong with Yu Na?

194
00:13:15,600 --> 00:13:17,300
What about me? Why?

195
00:13:17,370 --> 00:13:22,170
Not being able to bury the talisman
the other day definitely jinxed us.

196
00:13:22,940 --> 00:13:25,580
See?
You're just picking at your food.

197
00:13:25,610 --> 00:13:28,380
No wonder you collapsed
and ended up in the hospital.

198
00:13:29,180 --> 00:13:32,220
Now, tell me the truth.
What happened last night?

199
00:13:32,420 --> 00:13:35,490
I told you. I collapsed
and was taken to the hospital.

200
00:13:35,590 --> 00:13:39,990
Don't tell me this has something to do
with the Adele family mess.

201
00:13:41,990 --> 00:13:42,990
It doesn't.

202
00:13:42,990 --> 00:13:45,260
There's no need to be so down.

203
00:13:46,160 --> 00:13:50,700
You can always find another job,
and you'll meet someone better.

204
00:13:50,770 --> 00:13:52,770
Would you listen to that?

205
00:13:52,970 --> 00:13:56,770
For once,
you're actually making some sense.

206
00:13:57,110 --> 00:13:58,480
That's right, honey.

207
00:13:58,740 --> 00:14:01,550
After seeing
the kind of person Park Tae Ho is,

208
00:14:01,650 --> 00:14:04,950
you'd better not let him
anywhere near you. You hear me?

209
00:14:05,680 --> 00:14:09,990
Stay away from him and his family.
Got it?

210
00:14:11,220 --> 00:14:12,560
Goodness.

211
00:14:13,520 --> 00:14:14,660
Man, this is delicious.

212
00:14:16,460 --> 00:14:17,860
- Dig in.
- I will.

213
00:14:29,510 --> 00:14:31,910
Lure Chloe to the Adele warehouse.

214
00:14:32,540 --> 00:14:34,880
Use a fake meeting between Mr. Park
and Assemblyman Kwon tomorrow...

215
00:14:34,980 --> 00:14:36,810
as bait.

216
00:14:40,850 --> 00:14:42,790
I have no choice
but to do as she says.

217
00:14:45,420 --> 00:14:46,890
I'm just luring her there.

218
00:14:47,860 --> 00:14:49,230
That's all I have to do.

219
00:15:02,710 --> 00:15:04,010
You actually came into the office?

220
00:15:05,780 --> 00:15:06,980
Aren't you scared?

221
00:15:08,050 --> 00:15:10,810
I can't just cower at home, can I?

222
00:15:11,650 --> 00:15:13,450
Not when I have important business
to take care of.

223
00:15:14,150 --> 00:15:15,520
I need to be ready.

224
00:15:22,930 --> 00:15:24,530
(Adele warehouse, 12th, 9 p.m.)

225
00:15:25,800 --> 00:15:29,570
Apparently, Chairman Park is making
a secret deal tomorrow night.

226
00:15:30,400 --> 00:15:33,440
He's supposed to give a lot of money
to Assemblyman Kwon Yong Gil.

227
00:15:34,310 --> 00:15:37,210
It's a secret meeting
in a secluded place.

228
00:15:37,710 --> 00:15:38,880
Isn't this the perfect opportunity
for us?

229
00:15:40,380 --> 00:15:41,710
We could get there early...

230
00:15:41,710 --> 00:15:44,080
and set a trap for them,
just like they did to me.

231
00:15:45,620 --> 00:15:46,680
What do you think?

232
00:15:47,550 --> 00:15:48,550
(Adele warehouse, 12th, 9 p.m.)

233
00:15:49,690 --> 00:15:51,960
How did you get this information?

234
00:15:53,020 --> 00:15:54,060
Well...

235
00:15:55,560 --> 00:15:57,900
I had someone look into
the chairman's wife.

236
00:15:58,260 --> 00:15:59,430
The chairman's wife?

237
00:16:00,200 --> 00:16:04,500
If we're going after Chairman Park,
his secret appointments are the key.

238
00:16:05,370 --> 00:16:09,440
Ms. Oh usually handles them,
so I had someone investigate her.

239
00:16:10,410 --> 00:16:11,480
To be honest,

240
00:16:12,010 --> 00:16:15,280
I can't trust any time or place
that you set up.

241
00:16:15,680 --> 00:16:16,710
Am I supposed...

242
00:16:17,480 --> 00:16:19,680
to blindly trust your intel?

243
00:16:21,750 --> 00:16:25,120
If you don't believe me,
confirm the schedule yourself.

244
00:16:27,020 --> 00:16:29,090
If we miss this chance,
there won't be another one.

245
00:16:29,630 --> 00:16:31,230
If this fails,

246
00:16:32,630 --> 00:16:34,060
I'm going to give up.

247
00:16:35,130 --> 00:16:36,470
You're going to give up?

248
00:16:37,800 --> 00:16:40,240
It's not like we can do this
over and over.

249
00:16:41,470 --> 00:16:44,910
If we fail,
I'm giving up and running away.

250
00:16:46,340 --> 00:16:48,510
This is our first and last chance,

251
00:16:50,080 --> 00:16:51,250
so don't be late.

252
00:16:58,560 --> 00:17:00,690
She doesn't trust me to handle it.

253
00:17:02,290 --> 00:17:03,730
That's Choi Yu Na for you,

254
00:17:05,260 --> 00:17:07,930
but is it really safe for me
to go along with her plan?

255
00:17:13,740 --> 00:17:15,210
(James)

256
00:17:18,080 --> 00:17:21,310
James would call it too dangerous
and try to stop me.

257
00:17:22,880 --> 00:17:25,950
To confirm whether this is real...

258
00:17:34,460 --> 00:17:35,460
How dare you...

259
00:17:36,460 --> 00:17:38,000
make me come all the way out here?

260
00:17:39,100 --> 00:17:40,330
And yet, here you are.

261
00:17:41,100 --> 00:17:43,400
You said it was about the wedding
and that I had to be here.

262
00:17:45,070 --> 00:17:47,140
This had better be important.

263
00:17:47,770 --> 00:17:51,110
How about having dinner
with the chairman tomorrow?

264
00:17:51,410 --> 00:17:52,480
Like a gathering
between the families.

265
00:17:52,480 --> 00:17:55,510
Either it's a family gathering
or it's not. Why say "like?"

266
00:17:57,450 --> 00:17:59,850
Have you even discussed this
with Hyun Jun?

267
00:18:00,580 --> 00:18:02,790
I wanted to get
your permission first, ma'am.

268
00:18:04,020 --> 00:18:05,060
I see.

269
00:18:06,690 --> 00:18:08,430
I'm sure you've heard
the rumors about me,

270
00:18:08,890 --> 00:18:10,930
yet you still want to share
a meal with me?

271
00:18:11,460 --> 00:18:13,100
They're just rumors.

272
00:18:14,500 --> 00:18:18,340
Well, those rumors have
completely ruined my appetite.

273
00:18:19,040 --> 00:18:22,540
Besides, the chairman has a very
important meeting tomorrow.

274
00:18:23,270 --> 00:18:25,010
An important meeting?

275
00:18:25,010 --> 00:18:26,140
That's right.

276
00:18:26,540 --> 00:18:29,180
It's for a business rights contract
the chairman has worked hard on.

277
00:18:30,310 --> 00:18:33,980
He's meeting with
an important assemblyman over it,

278
00:18:33,980 --> 00:18:35,120
so stay out of it.

279
00:18:35,350 --> 00:18:36,590
And a family gathering?

280
00:18:37,690 --> 00:18:40,220
It's not happening anytime soon,
just so you know.

281
00:18:41,290 --> 00:18:42,460
And one more thing.

282
00:18:42,930 --> 00:18:44,630
I really...

283
00:18:45,330 --> 00:18:46,400
can't stand you.

284
00:19:07,250 --> 00:19:11,160
A business rights contract
with an important assemblyman?

285
00:19:13,160 --> 00:19:16,660
So Choi Yu Na's intel is solid.

286
00:19:21,230 --> 00:19:22,230
Jung Ran.

287
00:19:23,200 --> 00:19:25,200
Did it go well with Chloe?

288
00:19:25,700 --> 00:19:28,570
Don't tell me you got into
another hair-pulling catfight.

289
00:19:28,610 --> 00:19:31,010
If we had fought, do you think
I would've left so quietly?

290
00:19:31,510 --> 00:19:35,510
But you went in looking for a fight,
so seeing you come out like that...

291
00:19:35,610 --> 00:19:37,180
makes me even more nervous.

292
00:19:38,380 --> 00:19:41,890
It's all about to be over anyway.
Why waste my energy?

293
00:19:42,420 --> 00:19:43,750
What's about to be over?

294
00:19:45,020 --> 00:19:46,320
You don't need to know.

295
00:19:47,160 --> 00:19:49,930
Just do what I told you to do,
and do it right.

296
00:19:50,330 --> 00:19:52,530
The job you gave me?

297
00:19:53,160 --> 00:19:54,160
Booking a spa treatment?

298
00:19:54,160 --> 00:19:57,000
Time it exactly the way
I tell you to.

299
00:19:57,370 --> 00:19:59,870
- Got it?
- Yes, I got it.

300
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:03,470
You're being unusually
meticulous today.

301
00:20:10,980 --> 00:20:13,450
It's not just Park Min Jun.
It's you too.

302
00:20:14,180 --> 00:20:17,320
For Hyun Jun's sake,
it'd be better if you disappeared.

303
00:20:18,320 --> 00:20:19,660
Disappear without a trace...

304
00:20:20,290 --> 00:20:21,790
at the hands of Park Tae Ho.

305
00:20:24,490 --> 00:20:25,700
Tomorrow night,

306
00:20:26,060 --> 00:20:28,170
Chairman Park is meeting
with Assemblyman Kwon?

307
00:20:28,300 --> 00:20:31,400
Yes. I overheard it
while monitoring Oh Jung Ran.

308
00:20:32,000 --> 00:20:33,640
Chloe asked
if they could have dinner...

309
00:20:33,640 --> 00:20:35,270
with Chairman Park tomorrow night,

310
00:20:35,510 --> 00:20:37,540
but she said
he already had a meeting...

311
00:20:37,640 --> 00:20:39,540
with an assemblyman
about a contract.

312
00:20:40,510 --> 00:20:43,010
If it's about a business contract,
it has to be Assemblyman Kwon.

313
00:20:43,450 --> 00:20:46,750
But should he be meeting
with Mr. Kwon without your knowledge?

314
00:20:47,990 --> 00:20:51,690
I was kept in the dark,
but Oh Jung Ran wasn't.

315
00:20:52,790 --> 00:20:54,220
It looks like Chairman Park
and Oh Jung Ran...

316
00:20:54,220 --> 00:20:56,660
are scheming behind your back again.

317
00:20:57,290 --> 00:21:00,730
We must find out their plan
and stop them, no matter what.

318
00:21:01,770 --> 00:21:04,770
Find out where Chairman Park
and Mr. Kwon are meeting tomorrow.

319
00:21:05,540 --> 00:21:06,540
Sure.

320
00:21:11,310 --> 00:21:13,380
The Adele warehouse.

321
00:21:14,810 --> 00:21:16,910
It's the same place
where Choi Yu Na had her accident.

322
00:21:17,480 --> 00:21:20,450
Since it's a secluded property
owned by Adele Group,

323
00:21:20,720 --> 00:21:22,550
they can do whatever they want here.

324
00:21:23,620 --> 00:21:27,420
It's the perfect place
for Chairman Park's secret dealings.

325
00:21:28,730 --> 00:21:32,130
If he's meeting Assemblyman Kwon
in a place like this...

326
00:21:40,600 --> 00:21:44,010
(Consultant, Chloe Lee)

327
00:21:46,410 --> 00:21:49,280
How are you feeling?
Are you sure you should be at work?

328
00:21:50,450 --> 00:21:51,750
This is a professional setting.

329
00:21:52,150 --> 00:21:54,020
That kind of informal tone
is inappropriate.

330
00:21:55,590 --> 00:21:58,420
I'm sorry. I was worried,
and it just slipped out.

331
00:21:58,490 --> 00:22:02,130
That's all the more reason
not to worry about me.

332
00:22:08,070 --> 00:22:09,570
I won't give up.

333
00:22:09,700 --> 00:22:12,640
I'll stop you from doing
anything dangerous or reckless,

334
00:22:12,640 --> 00:22:14,810
and I won't let you
destroy yourself...

335
00:22:15,540 --> 00:22:16,770
over this quest for revenge.

336
00:22:18,280 --> 00:22:19,840
I'm not giving up either.

337
00:22:20,480 --> 00:22:21,980
No matter what you say,

338
00:22:22,810 --> 00:22:24,950
I'm going to see this through
to the very end.

339
00:22:37,930 --> 00:22:40,160
If Chloe believes me
and actually shows up,

340
00:22:40,660 --> 00:22:42,770
does that mean
Chairman Park will kill her,

341
00:22:43,100 --> 00:22:45,000
just like he did Baek Jin Ju?

342
00:22:46,800 --> 00:22:48,470
But still, I have to survive.

343
00:22:49,110 --> 00:22:51,340
It's either Chloe or me,

344
00:22:52,410 --> 00:22:53,910
and I intend to live.

345
00:23:08,230 --> 00:23:09,660
You seemed so suspicious,

346
00:23:10,290 --> 00:23:11,290
yet here you are.

347
00:23:11,630 --> 00:23:14,600
It didn't seem like your intel
was entirely fake.

348
00:23:15,200 --> 00:23:19,270
And this also seemed like a place
Chairman Park uses often.

349
00:23:21,340 --> 00:23:24,210
As for where
he and Assemblyman Kwon might meet,

350
00:23:24,780 --> 00:23:27,840
these two places
are the most likely.

351
00:23:28,380 --> 00:23:31,110
Our plan is to hit them back
the same way they came after us...

352
00:23:31,520 --> 00:23:33,880
and figure out an escape route
after the accident.

353
00:23:34,250 --> 00:23:35,620
Let's check the locations first.

354
00:23:47,060 --> 00:23:49,170
Come on. We don't have all day.

355
00:23:49,900 --> 00:23:50,900
Let's hurry.

356
00:23:55,440 --> 00:23:56,870
There's no need!

357
00:24:24,770 --> 00:24:25,940
Choi Yu Na.

358
00:24:26,600 --> 00:24:29,510
Don't blame Ms. Choi.

359
00:24:30,370 --> 00:24:33,010
To survive,
you have to know which side to take,

360
00:24:33,640 --> 00:24:35,480
and she made the right choice.

361
00:24:36,610 --> 00:24:39,450
I don't know what Ms. Choi told you,

362
00:24:39,980 --> 00:24:41,220
but you've been deceived.

363
00:24:41,790 --> 00:24:43,020
Deceived?

364
00:24:44,120 --> 00:24:45,120
Me?

365
00:24:45,720 --> 00:24:48,590
No way, sir. I didn't deceive you.

366
00:24:49,630 --> 00:24:51,260
Chloe's the one who's lying again.

367
00:24:51,330 --> 00:24:54,730
Think about it.
How has she acted all this time?

368
00:24:55,170 --> 00:24:56,900
Are you really going
to fall for it again?

369
00:24:58,130 --> 00:25:00,440
Well, this whole time...

370
00:25:02,040 --> 00:25:04,240
It's you who's been deceiving me.

371
00:25:04,240 --> 00:25:06,610
I heard what you said to her...

372
00:25:06,680 --> 00:25:07,810
myself.

373
00:25:08,410 --> 00:25:10,650
How dare you go after
Adele's bio division,

374
00:25:11,250 --> 00:25:15,620
and how dare you come after my life?

375
00:25:25,630 --> 00:25:26,730
I'm right, aren't I?

376
00:25:27,160 --> 00:25:29,070
You have feelings for Chloe too,
don't you?

377
00:25:30,870 --> 00:25:34,170
This is my private life.
It's none of your business.

378
00:25:36,640 --> 00:25:37,740
Your private life?

379
00:25:39,010 --> 00:25:41,750
Right. A dirty one at that.

380
00:25:42,650 --> 00:25:45,750
She's the woman
who's supposed to marry my Hyun Jun,

381
00:25:46,150 --> 00:25:49,450
and you still had the audacity
to try to steal her?

382
00:25:50,750 --> 00:25:54,890
Going after someone else's woman?
Did your mother teach you that?

383
00:25:54,890 --> 00:25:56,460
Please watch what you're saying.

384
00:25:56,460 --> 00:25:59,400
Talk about being defensive.
Who do you think you're yelling at?

385
00:26:02,570 --> 00:26:03,570
Whatever.

386
00:26:05,500 --> 00:26:08,310
Besides, Chloe is finished now.

387
00:26:10,870 --> 00:26:12,380
What's that supposed to mean?

388
00:26:13,610 --> 00:26:14,880
How Chloe...

389
00:26:15,550 --> 00:26:18,080
has been greedy
for the bio division...

390
00:26:18,550 --> 00:26:21,520
and even had the nerve
to try to kill the chairman?

391
00:26:24,020 --> 00:26:26,860
Well, the chairman found out
all about it.

392
00:26:28,730 --> 00:26:31,430
As for Chloe, she's as good as dead.

393
00:26:33,700 --> 00:26:34,700
Dead?

394
00:26:35,670 --> 00:26:37,930
- Father is going to hurt her?
- Of course.

395
00:26:38,230 --> 00:26:41,370
Do you think he'll let her live
when she's been after him?

396
00:26:42,440 --> 00:26:46,080
Where's Father right now?
Where's Chloe?

397
00:26:46,840 --> 00:26:49,380
Why?
So you can run off and save her?

398
00:26:50,410 --> 00:26:52,820
Tell me right now! Where is she?

399
00:26:53,920 --> 00:26:57,450
At the Adele warehouse, I believe.

400
00:26:58,560 --> 00:27:00,020
There are plenty of places there...

401
00:27:00,290 --> 00:27:02,130
to kill someone and bury the body.

402
00:27:09,400 --> 00:27:12,270
He's reacting even more strongly
than I expected.

403
00:27:14,340 --> 00:27:17,810
He's not just fond of her.
He's desperately in love.

404
00:27:20,480 --> 00:27:21,480
Sure.

405
00:27:22,210 --> 00:27:24,110
I suppose the two of them meeting
in the afterlife...

406
00:27:24,880 --> 00:27:26,250
wouldn't be so bad.

407
00:27:46,440 --> 00:27:48,270
Have you figured out
where they're meeting?

408
00:27:48,270 --> 00:27:50,710
That's the strange part.

409
00:27:51,140 --> 00:27:52,880
I checked
with Assemblyman Kwon's office,

410
00:27:52,880 --> 00:27:54,610
and there's no meeting scheduled
with Chairman Park.

411
00:27:54,740 --> 00:27:55,850
What?

412
00:27:56,980 --> 00:27:59,050
Could they have lied
to throw us off?

413
00:27:59,150 --> 00:28:00,320
I don't know.

414
00:28:01,720 --> 00:28:03,290
I don't get what's going on.

415
00:28:04,090 --> 00:28:05,160
What about Chairman Park?

416
00:28:05,160 --> 00:28:06,860
He's not in his office right now.

417
00:28:06,990 --> 00:28:10,460
Try again and find him.
Find out what he's up to.

418
00:28:10,860 --> 00:28:11,860
Got it.

419
00:28:17,370 --> 00:28:18,970
Butler Ok?

420
00:28:20,970 --> 00:28:24,510
- Yes?
- Head to the Adele warehouse.

421
00:28:24,870 --> 00:28:25,880
What?

422
00:28:27,110 --> 00:28:31,350
Mr. Min Jun went to the warehouse,
and I have a bad feeling about it.

423
00:28:31,710 --> 00:28:34,180
It could be dangerous.
Please, hurry.

424
00:28:38,920 --> 00:28:41,490
The warehouse? It's dangerous?

425
00:28:42,290 --> 00:28:43,790
Min Jun's in danger?

426
00:28:44,290 --> 00:28:47,130
No, not Min Jun!

427
00:29:18,660 --> 00:29:19,800
Ms. Choi.

428
00:29:21,160 --> 00:29:23,330
You finish this.

429
00:29:24,800 --> 00:29:25,800
Sir...

430
00:29:27,200 --> 00:29:29,270
You need to see this through
with me...

431
00:29:30,340 --> 00:29:32,410
so I can finally feel at ease...

432
00:29:33,210 --> 00:29:34,980
knowing you're on my side.

433
00:29:36,780 --> 00:29:38,380
Go on. Finish her!

434
00:30:23,330 --> 00:30:24,330
Choi Yu Na.

435
00:30:28,800 --> 00:30:31,970
If you kill me, you're next.

436
00:30:42,910 --> 00:30:44,110
Ms. Choi!

437
00:30:57,160 --> 00:30:59,330
Yu Na!

438
00:31:31,960 --> 00:31:33,930
What are you waiting for? Get her!

439
00:31:35,800 --> 00:31:37,070
- After her!
- Go!

440
00:31:37,870 --> 00:31:39,670
- Stop right there!
- Go find her.

441
00:31:41,170 --> 00:31:45,140
Get her, you punks. Get her, now!

442
00:31:45,210 --> 00:31:46,210
Shut the door!

443
00:31:51,250 --> 00:31:52,980
What are you all doing?
Block the doors!

444
00:32:04,190 --> 00:32:05,800
- Get her.
- Get her, you idiots!

445
00:32:05,960 --> 00:32:07,230
Hurry, go get her!

446
00:32:07,600 --> 00:32:08,630
Darn it.

447
00:32:50,270 --> 00:32:53,240
(Pearl in Red)

448
00:32:53,640 --> 00:32:56,380
- Call the police right now.
- Min Jun!

449
00:32:56,450 --> 00:33:00,320
Tell them to catch the punk
who did this to my son!

450
00:33:00,320 --> 00:33:04,390
Mrs. Ok, please tell me.
Why did you call me and say that?

451
00:33:04,390 --> 00:33:06,620
Please, just be honest
and tell me what you know.

452
00:33:06,790 --> 00:33:09,230
How did Min Jun and Chloe end up
in that accident together?

453
00:33:09,490 --> 00:33:10,790
What was that car about?

454
00:33:10,790 --> 00:33:12,560
It didn't seem
like Chairman Park knew either.

455
00:33:13,100 --> 00:33:15,730
Or was I a target too?

456
00:33:15,830 --> 00:33:17,830
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
